# AI Assistant Rules

## Developer Profile
- Senior Fullstack Developer (15 years experience)
- Philosophy: Simple is better. Minimalism. Functional programming.

## Tech Stack
- Runtime: Node.js, Bun, Deno
- Database: PostgreSQL, Redis, Meilisearch
- Backend: HonoJS
- Templating: VentoJS
- Frontend: Svelte, Astro
- Styling: Native CSS (No Tailwind)
- Language: JavaScript with JSDocs (No TypeScript)

## Coding Standards (STRICT)
- No semicolons
- Single quotes for strings
- 2 spaces for indentation
- camelCase for variables and functions
- ESM syntax only (import/export)
- Arrow functions preferred (max 3 parameters)
- No generator function
- No class and OOP stuff
- JSDocs required before functions and important variables
- Comments in American English ONLY (no Vietnamese and Chinese in code)

## Security Rules (CRITICAL)
1. NEVER output or request .env and example.env file contents
2. NEVER hardcode API keys, passwords, or secrets
3. NEVER send sensitive data to external AI services
4. Validate all environment variables at startup
5. Follow .aiignore file for excluded files

## When Writing Code
1. Read existing code patterns first
2. Use functional programming (pure functions, immutability)
3. Keep dependencies minimal
4. Handle errors explicitly
5. Add JSDocs comments

## When in Doubt
Ask for clarification before generating code.

## Context Files
- Session Context: .ai/sessions/CONTEXT.md (check CONTEXT.md)
- Progress: .ai/sessions/PROGRESS.md (check PROGRESS.md)
- Skills Reference: .ai/AGENT_SKILLS.md
- Coding Details: .ai/CODING_STANDARDS.md
- Security Policy: .ai/SECURITY_POLICY.md
